JOHANNESBURG - Groceries made up the biggest part of spending by South Africans in December. South Africans spent a total of R51.5-billion that month, R5-billion more than during December 2016, according to Africa’s largest automated payments clearing house, BankServe. READ: Black Friday exceeds economists' expectations But the real eye-catcher of BankServe’s latest survey is that it recorded the highest number of swipes by an individual in the December period - at 1,160 swipes. The biggest single transaction by an individual was R5-million. eNCA